<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="508" pageId="6" pageNumber="505" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1902,2035]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,151,1151]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="508" pageId="6" pageNumber="505">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1902,1927]" pageId="6" pageNumber="505">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is distinguished from congeners by the following combination of characters: Generally very dark brown, shiny; small to moderately small shore flies, body length 
<quantity box="[1033,1203,1939,1963]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8499999999999999" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="505" unit="mm" value="1.8499999999999999" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="1.4">1.40–2.30 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[1217,1278,1938,1963]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="505">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1296,1423,1938,1963]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 10" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1974,1997]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,589,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,589,1953]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 10. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (8) Head, anterior view; (9) Same, lateral view; (10) Same, oblique view. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254467/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="505">
Figs. 
<number box="[1363,1423,1939,1963]" pageId="6" pageNumber="505" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8–10</number>
</figureCitation>
): Frons microtomentose brown on black background. Basal flagellomere mostly blackish, especially dorsoapically, only basoventromost portion yellowish, gradually tapered to rounded apex; arista with 
<number box="[1171,1227,2011,2035]" pageId="6" pageNumber="505" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10</number>
dorsal rays. Face mostly shiny bluish black to black, conspicuously microsculptured with shallow, mostly vertical and transverse striae. Eye ratio: 
<number box="[343,438,188,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="506" value="37.295" valueMax="74.0" valueMin="0.59">0.59–74</number>
; gena-to-eye ratio: 
<number box="[656,771,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="506" value="0.125" valueMax="0.14" valueMin="0.11">0.11–0.14</number>
. 
<emphasis box="[781,871,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="506">Thorax:</emphasis>
Mesonotum sparsely microtomentose with brown microtomentum on shiny black background, appearing subshiny; anepisternum mostly shiny, only extreme margins microtomentose. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[424,507,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 51" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1199,1222]" captionTargetBox="[162,1420,234,1150]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[153,1433,227,1162]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 51. Wings: (46) Mimapsilopa xingu n. sp.; (47) Mimapsilopa rugosa n. sp.; (48) Mimapsilopa onssa n. sp.; (49). Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp.; (50). Mimapsilopa acta n. sp.; (51). Mimapsilopa plaumanni n. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254477/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="506">
Fig. 
<number box="[478,507,260,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="506" value="49.0">49</number>
</figureCitation>
) mostly infuscate, anterior margin brown, becoming progressively lighter colored posteriorly, posterior margin largely hyaline; length 
<quantity box="[736,902,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="506" unit="mm" value="1.85" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="1.5">1.50–2.20 mm</quantity>
; costal ratio 
<number box="[1044,1159,295,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="506" value="0.6299999999999999" valueMax="0.69" valueMin="0.57">0.57–0.69</number>
; M vein ratio 
<number box="[1317,1433,296,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="506" value="0.8200000000000001" valueMax="0.91" valueMin="0.73">0.73–0.91</number>
. Knob of halter white, stem yellowish. Foreleg, including forebasitarsomere and femora, and tibiae of mid- and hindlegs dark brown to black; extreme apex of mid- and hindtibiae and mid- and hindtarsi yellow except for darkened apical tarsomere. 
<emphasis box="[461,576,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="506">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Tergites sparsely microtomentose, mostly shiny; tergites 4, 5 about equal in length, both longer than tergite 
<number box="[503,519,440,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="506" value="3.0">3</number>
; tergite 
<number box="[610,624,439,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="506" value="5.0">5</number>
bare, shiny. Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[959,1096,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="506">
Figs. 
<number box="[1022,1096,439,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="506" value="13.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="11.0">11–15</number>
</figureCitation>
): Epandrium in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[159,239,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="506">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,239,476,500]" pageId="7" pageNumber="506" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) setulose with short, moderately stout setulae, shape as an inverted, thick-walled U, widest at dorsolateral corners, conspicuously thinner at dorsal portion above cercal cavity, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1095,1176,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="506">
Fig. 
<number box="[1147,1176,512,536]" pageId="7" pageNumber="506" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) height double width, anterior margin sinuous and with sub-basal short projection, posterior margin nearly straight; cercus in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[221,302,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[275,302,188,212]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) elongate, shallowly lunate but not sharply pointed at ventral and dorsal apices, in lateral view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,224,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) semi-hemispherical; presurstylus symmetrical, robust, in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[1030,1111,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[1084,1111,224,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) with one short medial lobe bearing an apical, stout setulae, thereafter ventrally robustly developed, ventral margin rounded, slightly tapered in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[304,389,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[360,389,296,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) quadrate on basal half, thereafter apically with short, thumb-like, broadly rounded apical process; postsurstylus symmetrical, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[738,821,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[791,821,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
), elongate, moderately narrow, sinuous, bearing short, fringe-like setulae on posterior margin, in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[816,902,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[873,902,368,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
) pointed medially, angulate subapically, apex truncate, lacking a rod-like, extended process; subepandrial plate in ventral view moderately and widely U-shaped, lateral arms recurved, tapered toward apex, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[835,918,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[889,918,439,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
) as a parallelogram; aedeagus in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[217,245,476,501]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
) somewhat rectangular on basal half, apical portion narrower, digitiform, apex narrowly rounded, in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[308,390,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[361,390,512,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
) elongate, base ovate, apical third abruptly narrowed, narrowly digitiform; phallapodeme in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[306,390,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[362,390,548,573]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
) broadly helmut-like, extended keel wide and moderately high, in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1342,1428,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
