<number box="[1399,1428,548,572]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
) elongate, slender, T-shaped; pregonite fused, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[840,921,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
