<number box="[893,921,583,608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
) a curved, rod-like process, bearing 
<number box="[1336,1350,584,608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="2.0">2</number>
setulae apically; hypandrium in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[616,705,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[676,705,620,644]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
) broadly and robustly semi-circular, anterior margin broadly rounded, laterobasal margin with angulate extension, thereafter posteriorly narrowed, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1342,1428,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Mimapsilopa iguassu n. sp. (11) Epandrium, cerci, presurstylus, posterior view. (12) Same, lateral view. (13) Postsurstyli and postsurstylar process. (14) Aedeagus, hypandrium, phallapodeme, pregonite, subepandrial plate, ventral view. (15) Same, postsurstylus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254468/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
Fig. 
<number box="[1399,1428,655,680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" value="15.0">15</number>
