<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="508" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1151]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,982,1007]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet, 
<emphasis box="[584,676,983,1006]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
<taxonomicName box="[584,672,983,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Mimapsilopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iguassu">iguassu</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
refers to the 
<typeStatus box="[839,887,983,1007]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">type</typeStatus>
locality, Parque Iguaçu, in the Municipality of Curitiba, 
<collectingCountry box="[257,328,1018,1043]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="508" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1151]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1054,1079]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Remarks.</emphasis>
Externally this species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[732,820,1055,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Mimapsilopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acta">
<emphasis box="[732,820,1055,1078]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">M. acta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished from it and other congeners, especially those of the 
<taxonomicName box="[429,521,1092,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Mimapsilopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cressoni">
<emphasis box="[429,521,1092,1115]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">cressoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, by the coloration and shape of the basal flagellomere, the pattern of infuscation of the wing, and by structures of the male terminalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
